citeinfo.title: ECC Dispatch Areas, Ramsey County, Minnesota

descript.abstract: This dataset contains polygons that represent areas for dispatching law enforcement, fire and emergency medical services by Ramsey County Emergency Communications. The polygons match the vendor specific hierarchy, in the computer aided dispatch system used by Ramsey County Emergency Communications.
descript.purpose: This data set is specially supports a better understanding of the open data published by the County related to emergency communications dispatch.

theme.themekey: boundaries, computer aided dispatch areas, battalion, law enforcement, fire and emergency medical services

overview.eaover: This polygon data set specifically supports data published by Ramsey County Emergency Communications Center (RC ECC), on Ramsey Countys Open Data Portal. Each polygon represents an area for aggregating 9-1-1 incident locations. The categorization of these areas is specific to the Computer Aided Dispatch software vendor utilized by the RC ECC.

horizpa.horizpar: Digitized information is generally +/- 7 feet; some areas have been found to be +/- 30 feet.

attracc.attraccr: These areas represent where an incident was geo validated, and in most cases the public safety agency that responded to the incident.
